      "settings": {
        "width": "full-width",
        "title": "",
        "text": "<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>1) What is an LED light stick used for?</h3><p>An <strong>LED Light Stick</strong> is used to add slim, linear lighting to a vehicle for visibility, warning, or support lighting. It’s popular for grilles, bumpers, rear doors, and racks because it provides a wide light surface in a low-profile form.</p><h3>2) Is a car light stick different from a truck light stick?</h3><p>A <strong>Car Light Stick</strong> and a truck light stick can be the same type of product—the difference is usually mounting space and placement. Cars often need slimmer, shorter options due to tighter mounting areas.</p><h3>3) Where should I mount an LED light stick for best visibility?</h3><p>Common locations include the grille or bumper for forward visibility and the tailgate or rear door for rear visibility. Side placements can improve awareness on job sites or when parked roadside.</p><h3>4) Can I use multiple LED light sticks on one vehicle?</h3><p>Yes. Many builds use multiple <strong>LED Light Stick</strong> units to create front-and-rear coverage or to add side visibility. This can provide more complete awareness than a single light in one location.</p><h3>5) Do LED light sticks work as a standalone warning system?</h3><p>They can for basic visibility, but higher-risk work often benefits from layered lighting—combining light sticks with other <strong>Warning Lights</strong> or <strong>LED Light Bars</strong> for broader coverage and redundancy.</p>",
        "heading_size": "medium",
        "text_alignment": "left"
      }
